ers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-compost%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecomposting%3C%2Fa%3E%20waste%20on-site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Rabia%20Sottil%20and%20his%20team%20prepare%20for%20the%20festive%20season%2C%20they're%20building%20a%20breakfast%20buffet%20that%20includes%20beloved%20classics%20with%20smart%20tech%20to%20cut%20leftovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20it%20all%20is%20building%20more%20mindful%20dining%20practices.%20%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20is%20to%20create%20that%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-food-waste-management-chefs-hotel-menus-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756913795000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b1c12f194a2d49b8af6e53%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-food-waste-management-chefs-hotel-menus-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chefs%20at%20hotels%20are%20using%20AI%20food-waste%20management%20tools%2C%20like%20Winnow%2C%20to%20cut%20kitchen%20scraps%2C%20slash%20costs%2C%20and%20turn%20leftovers%20into%20creative%20dishes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Chloe%20Pantazi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-food-waste-management-chefs-hotel-menus-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google's%20antitrust%20win%20is%20an%20L%20for%20everyone%20else%20who%20sells%20ads%20online%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Google%20logo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8aaa843bb77284b9dfecc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222553%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai.%3Cp%3EChristoph%20Soeder%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle's%20search%20antitrust%20trial%20ruling%20is%20a%20win%20for%20the%20tech%20giant%2C%20but%20a%20loss%20for%20many%20websites.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20was%20spared%20from%20divesting%20its%20Chrome%20browser%20and%20other%20major%20remedies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt'll%20have%20to%20share%20search%20data%20with%20AI%20rivals%2C%20which%20could%20accelerate%20web%20traffic%20declines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20day%2C%20another%20win%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20hopes%20within%20the%20online%20ad%20industry%20that%20the%20courts%20would%20make%20the%20search%20giant%20a%20weaker%20advertising%20competitor%2C%20or%20the%20industry%20less%20reliant%20on%20it%2C%20were%20dashed%20this%20week%20by%20Judge%20Amit%20P.%20Mehta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20escaped%20having%20to%20divest%20its%20Chrome%20browser%20or%20Android%20operating%20system%2C%20the%20biggest%20remedies%20sought%20by%20the%20US%20government%20in%20the%20tech%20giant's%20landmark%20online%20search%20antitrust%20case.%20A%20breakup%20would%20have%20been%20a%20huge%20blow%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-sell-chrome-search-winners-losers-doj-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20advertising%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cutting%20off%20key%20distribution%20points%20that%20help%20it%20collect%20mountains%20of%20user%20data%20and%20sell%20high-value%20targeted%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20didn't%20come%20out%20of%20the%20yearslong%20trial%20entirely%20unscathed%3A%20It%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-antitrust-monopoly-doj-ruling-decision-chrome-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebarred%20from%20entering%20exclusive%20contracts%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20platforms%20like%20Apple%20to%20make%20it%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20phones%20and%20browsers%20(Google%20can%20still%20strike%20non-exclusive%20deals%20to%20get%20products%20like%20search%20or%20Gemini%20preloaded%2C%20the%20judge%20said).%20It%20will%20also%20be%20forced%20to%20share%20some%20search%20data%20and%20syndication%20services%20with%20its%20rivals%2C%20though%20this%20doesn't%20extend%20to%20advertising%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20generally%20saw%20Tuesday's%20ruling%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-antitrust-monopoly-case-decision-winners-losers-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebest-case%20scenario%20for%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20now%2C%20Google's%20big%20fort%20on%20the%20hill%20is%20intact%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matt%20Wilk%C3%A9%2C%20head%20of%20digital%20partnerships%20at%20the%20media%20agency%20Mediaplus%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20companies%20that%20make%20up%20the%20online%20advertising%20ecosystem%2C%20it's%20a%20reminder%20that%20making%20money%20from%20selling%20ads%20on%20the%20web%20is%20getting%20harder%20every%20day.%20Google's%20dominance%20in%20traditional%20search%20advertising%20remains.%20And%20the%20move%20to%20force%20Google%20to%20share%20its%20search%20data%20with%20generative%20AI%20rivals%20could%20accelerate%20traffic%20declines%20as%20users%20opt%20for%20chatbot%20answers%20over%20website%20clicks%2C%20ad%20industry%20insiders%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20bad%20for%20news%20websites%2C%20blogs%2C%20and%20other%20content%20publishers%20because%20it%20gives%20them%20fewer%20opportunities%20to%20serve%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decision%20is%20a%20huge%20win%20for%20Google%20and%20tough%20on%20the%20broader%20adtech%20ecosystem%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stephen%20Upstone%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20adtech%20company%20LoopMe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20declined%20to%20comment.%20In%20a%20blog%20post%20published%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20company%20said%20the%20court%20had%20recognized%20that%20divesting%20Chrome%20and%20Android%20would%20have%20harmed%20consumers%20and%20partners.%20Google%20said%20it%20had%20concerns%20about%20user%20privacy%20related%20to%20its%20requirement%20to%20share%20search%20data%20with%20rivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2213a80bf8-eca7-43ab-8be6-ae3ab8c9f79c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGenerative%20AI%20is%20the%20new%20search%20battleground%20%E2%80%94%20and%20publishers%20are%20backed%20into%20a%20corner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20ruling%2C%20Judge%20Mehta%20considered%20the%20changing%20search%20landscape%2C%20as%20users%20increasingly%20turn%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-save-google-doj-breakup-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%20chatbots%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20ChatGPT%2C%20Perplexity%2C%20and%20Claude%20rather%20than%20traditional%20search%20engines%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20publishers%20are%20grappling%20with%20how%20this%20shift%20in%20behavior%20could%20reduce%20traffic%20to%20their%20sites%2C%20which%20has%20a%20knock-on%20effect%20on%20their%20ad%20revenue.%20Davide%20Rosamilia%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20products%20at%20the%20adtech%20company%20ID5%2C%20said%20the%20remedy%20imposed%20on%20Google%20to%20share%20search%20index%20and%20user-interaction%20data%20with%20competitors%20could%20strengthen%20the%20generative%20AI%20landscape%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20publishers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20AI%20could%20more%20quickly%20bypass%20publisher%20sites%20altogether%2C%20pushing%20users%20into%20'zero-click'%20journeys%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosamilia%20said.%20%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20Google's%20walled%20garden%2C%20publishers%20could%20be%20staring%20at%20new%20ones%20built%20by%20giant%20AI%20companies%2C%20leaving%20publishers%20even%20further%20on%20the%20margins.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20publishers%20have%20also%20raised%20concerns%20that%20they%20have%20to%20let%20Google%20scrape%20their%20content%20for%20use%20in%20its%20generative%20AI%20products%20if%20they%20want%20their%20articles%20to%20appear%20on%20Google's%20traditional%20search%20results%20pages.%20Danielle%20Coffey%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-respond-googles-antitrust-lawsuit-remedies-chrome-ai-monopoly-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENews%2FMedia%20Alliance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20publisher%20trade%20body%20was%20disappointed%20that%20Judge%20Mehta's%20remedies%20didn't%20include%20%26quot%3Ban%20opt-out%20of%20AI%26quot%3B%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20leaves%20us%20with%20little%20options%20in%20the%20use%20of%20our%20content%20and%20little%20to%20no%20revenue%20for%20our%20quality%20journalism%2C%26quot%3B%20Coffey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvertisers%2C%20too%2C%20are%20having%20to%20adjust%20their%20strategies%20as%20AI%20tools%20become%20users'%20first%20stop%2C%20said%20Mitchell%20Feldman%2C%20chief%20executive%20of%20the%20marketing%20agency%20Jam%207.%20While%20traditional%20search%20remains%20the%20most%20popular%20way%20for%20people%20to%20find%20information%2C%20it%20might%20be%20displaced%20sooner%20than%20anticipated%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20old%20model%20of%20buying%20attention%20through%20keyword%20auctions%20and%20hoping%20for%20clicks%20is%20eroding%2C%26quot%3B%20Feldman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283c3c49d-de20-4e21-bd07-ff0ab242f095%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdvertisers%20and%20Google%20remain%20interlocked%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20ruling%20eases%20Google's%20grip%20just%20enough%20to%20let%20some%20search%20engines%20take%20nibbles%20at%20the%20edge%2C%20advertisers%20remain%20tied%20to%20Google%20for%20now%2C%20said%20Mediaplus%20UK's%20Wilk%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20is%20forecast%20to%20take%20a%2025.5%25%20share%20of%20the%20US%20digital%20ad%20market%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20EMARKETER.%20The%20majority%20of%20Google's%20ad%20revenue%20is%20derived%20from%20search%20ads.%20There%20is%20an%20upside%20to%20Google%20avoiding%20the%20worst%20potential%20remedies%3A%20A%20wholesale%20breakup%20of%20Google%20could%20have%20caused%20short-term%20pain%20for%20advertisers%20as%20they%20readjusted%20their%20ad-buying%20strategies%20across%20a%20web%20of%20smaller%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-analysts-google-antitrust-decision-take-favorable-benign-stock-target-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMorgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20data-sharing%20clauses%20in%20the%20antitrust%20ruling%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20benign%26quot%3B%20for%20Google's%20business%20because%20it%20will%20still%20require%20extensive%20investment%20for%20competitors%20to%20turn%20its%20raw%20data%20into%20something%20appealing%20for%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat'll%20be%20challenging%20for%20the%20AI%20companies%20because%20of%20Google's%20scale%20and%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it's%20already%20shown%20to%20improve%20and%20personalize%20its%20generative%20AI%20offerings%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20note%20on%20Wednesday.%20Google%20would%20have%20been%20more%20affected%20were%20it%20forced%20to%20share%20more%20proprietary%20data%20sets%20like%20its%20search%20page%20rank%20or%20ads%20data%2C%20which%20could%20help%20competitors%20optimize%20their%20own%20products%2C%20the%20analysts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShares%20of%20Google's%20parent%20company%2C%20Alphabet%2C%20rose%20about%208%25%20in%20morning%20trading%20on%20Wednesday%20as%20investors