2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20never%20a%20good%20day%20when%20an%20activist%20investor%20announces%20a%20big%20stake%20in%20your%20company%2C%20with%20a%20public%20campaign%20pointing%20out%20the%20flaws%20in%20your%20strategy%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPepsi's%20leadership%20got%20to%20experience%20the%20thrill%20of%20receiving%20a%20letter%20from%20billionaire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-singer-elliott-management-interview-risk-fun-hedge-fund-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPaul%20Singer's%20Elliott%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%20informing%20them%20that%20their%20sprawling%20conglomerate%20was%20underperforming%20on%20Tuesday.%20Elliott's%20%244%20billion%20stake%20in%20the%20consumer%20packaged%20goods%20and%20beverage%20behemoth%20comes%20with%20the%20expectation%20that%20changes%20will%20be%20made%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnack-prices-may-fall-after-years-of-inflation-pepsico-said-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPepsiCo%3C%2Fa%3E%20finds%20itself%20at%20a%20critical%20inflection%20point.%20The%20company%20has%20an%20opportunity%20%E2%80%94%20and%20an%20obligation%20%E2%80%94%20to%20improve%20financial%20performance%20and%20regain%20its%20position%20as%20an%20industry%20leader%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20reads%2C%20noting%20that%20Pepsi's%20stock%20could%20soar%20more%20than%2050%25%20if%20it%20follows%20the%20hedge%20fund's%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20different%20era%2C%20when%20Elliott%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-elliott-alums-are-launching-their-own-funds-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20less%20institutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20managed%20less%20than%20half%20the%20%2476%20billion%20in%20assets%20it%20boasts%20today%2C%20a%20letter%20like%20this%20would%20send%20chills%20down%20the%20spine%20of%20Pepsi%20CEO%20Ramon%20Laguarta.%20Now%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20growing%20scale%20of%20activists%2C%20the%20growth%20of%20corporate%20defense%20teams%20at%20investment%20banks%2C%20and%20regulatory%20tweaks%2C%20a%20campaign%20from%20a%20feared%20investor%20is%20closer%20to%20a%20McKinsey%20review%20than%20a%20corporate%20espionage-filled%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20there'll%20be%20costs%20that%20will%20be%20cut%20or%20units%20to%20be%20sold%2C%20but%20the%20old-school%20activist%20tactics%20such%20as%20pressuring%20the%20CEO%20to%20step%20down%2C%20which%20earned%20Singer%20the%20title%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2018%2F08%2F27%2Fpaul-singer-doomsday-investor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoomsday%20investor%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20New%20Yorker%20in%202018%2C%20are%20not%20go-to%20moves.%20That's%20in%20part%20because%20activists%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20power%20to%20board%20members%20and%20executives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkets%20almost%20always%20agree%20with%20activists%2C%20and%20Pepsi's%20stock%20price%20bump%20Tuesday%20on%20the%20news%20of%20Elliott's%20stake%20is%20the%20latest%20example.%20Investors%20in%20hedge%20funds%20believe%20activism%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20winning%20strategy%2C%20as%20these%20managers%20now%20run%20close%20to%20%24230%20billion%20industrywide%2C%20according%20to%20HFR%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2035%25%20since%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20activists%20don't%20even%20need%20to%20make%20noise%20to%20get%20a%20company%20to%20go%20along.%20A%20Barclays%20review%20of%20activist%20campaigns%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%20found%20that%20settlements%20between%20companies%20and%20investors%20had%20risen%20compared%20to%20last%20year%2C%20boosting%20board%20seats%20allotted%20to%20investors%20and%20their%20choices%20by%2016%25.%20Close%20to%20half%20of%20the%20settlements%20this%20year%20came%20without%20a%20public%20campaign%20from%20a%20hedge%20fund%2C%20Barclays%20said%2C%20compared%20to%2026%25%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlready%20this%20year%2C%20financial%20analytics%20firm%20Charles%20River%20settled%20with%20Elliott.%20While%20there%20will%20still%20be%20one-off%20campaigns%20that%20become%20more%20heated%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20Elliott's%20proxy%20fight%20with%20Phillips66%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnelson-peltz-disney-shares-proxy-battle-bob-iger-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrian's%20battle%20with%20Disney%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20big-name%20companies%20find%20it%20easier%20to%20rip%20the%20bandaid%20off%20than%20to%20fight%20what%20may%20end%20up%20being%20a%20losing%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarmen%20Lu%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Paul%20Weiss%20who%20defends%20companies%20targeted%20by%20activists%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%2013D%20Monitor%20report%20that%20%26quot%3Bmany%20repeat%20activists%20have%20now%20developed%20familiar%20playbooks%20that%20help%20guide%20parties%20to%20what%20kind%20of%20resolution%20might%20be%20possible%20earlier%20on%20in%20a%20campaign.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20very%20few%20directors%20at%20vulnerable%20companies%20who%20reflexively%20want%20to%20fight%20if%20a%20good%20settlement%20is%20available.%20This%20is%20a%20major%20change%20from%2020%20or%20even%20ten%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Lu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20especially%20true%20of%20the%20largest%20public%20companies%20that%20big-name%20investors%20target%20because%20they're%20the%20only%20ones%20big%20enough%20to%20move%20the%20needle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20column%20in%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F52c45941-87da-4f16-bec4-ae2d532b527d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20Pepsi%20campaign%20summed%20up%20the%20current%20state%20of%20mega-cap%20campaigns%3A%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20shareholder%20activism%20looks%20positively%20easy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20pred