the%20guest%20carries%20a%20bottle%20of%20wine%20with%20a%20bow%20on%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b0b62f194a2d49b8af6492%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20someone%20is%20giving%20you%20a%20gift%20as%20a%20'thank%20you'%2C%20sending%20a%20note%20back%20to%20them%20can%20be%20redundant.%3Cp%3EJacob%20Lund%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20an%20etiquette%20perspective%2C%20you%20technically%20do%20not%20need%20to%20send%20a%20thank-you%20note%20in%20response%20to%20a%20gift%20meant%20to%20act%20as%20a%20'thank%20you%2C'%20such%20as%20a%20host%20gift%2C%26quot%3B%20Grumet%20Humbert%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20gift%20is%20usually%20an%20expression%20of%20gratitude%2C%20so%20sending%20a%20thank-you%20note%20back%20can%20create%20a%20cycle%20of%20thanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20the%20thank-you%20gift%20is%20particularly%20thoughtful%20or%20sentimental%2C%20Grumet%20Humbert%20said%20you%20can%20send%20one%20anyway%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20probably%20not%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22863f6c3a-1af1-4d20-8914-976a87cb9d21%5C%22%3ESimilarly%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20writing%20a%20note%20after%20receiving%20a%20gift%20from%20a%20group%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMusayeva%20said%20a%20physical%20thank-you%20note%20isn't%20necessary%20after%20receiving%20a%20gift%20from%20a%20large%20group%2C%20such%20as%20a%20departure%20gift%20from%20your%20team%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20gift%20comes%20from%20a%20large%20group%2C%20it's%20acceptable%20to%20send%20one%20well-crafted%20email%20or%20message%20to%20the%20group%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20responding%20to%20a%20group%20card%20or%20collective%20effort%2C%26quot%3B%20Musayeva%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-you-sh